(51, 1, '2021-05-14 20:42:02', '2021-05-14 20:42:02', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hello and welcome to my blog. In this space I will be writing mostly about testing but also about other things that I like.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some of them could be:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Testing techniques</li><li>Test Automation tools like<ul><li>Cypress - <a href="https://cypress.io" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://cypress.io</a></li><li>Selenium/Webdriver - <a href="https://www.selenium.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://www.selenium.dev/</a></li><li>TestCafe - <a href="https://testcafe.io/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://testcafe.io/</a></li></ul></li><li>API Testing tools:<ul><li>Postman - <a href="https://www.postman.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://www.postman.com/</a></li><li>SuperTest - <a href="https://github.com/visionmedia/supertest" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">https://github.com/visionmedia/supertest</a></li></ul></li><li>Linux related stuff (commands, apps, etc)</li><li>Some other things like for example apps that I use to support my testing</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the beginning I will be writing once a week, and once I\'m use to it I would like to increase the frequency. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Considering that I\'m not a native English speaker, even though I\'m used to working using English as my main language, you could see some grammar or spelling errors. Constructive feedback is always welcome!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Hello! Welcome to my blog!', 'Hello and welcome to my blog. In this space I will be writing mostly about testing but also about other things that I like.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hello-welcome-to-my-blog', '', '', '2021-05-14 20:42:02', '2021-05-14 20:42:02', '', 0, 'http://152.44.33.220/?p=51', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(56, 1, '2021-05-25 20:56:55', '2021-05-25 20:56:55', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cypress is a front end testing tool, and according to its documentation, it will allow you to write:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>End to end tests (E2E)</li><li>Integration tests</li><li>Unit tests</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cypress is a desktop application that needs to be installed on your machine, the system requirements may vary depending on the OS that you are using. Go visit this link for more information: <a href="https://docs.cypress.io/guides/getting-started/installing-cypress#System-requirements" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" title="https://docs.cypress.io/guides/getting-started/installing-cypress#System-requirements">https://docs.cypress.io/guides/getting-started/installing-cypress#System-requirements</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Basically, you will need to have Node version 12 or above installed, and then you will be able to use npm to install it, these are the steps to do it:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->\n<ol><li>cd into your project folder: it needs to be a folder where you already ran npm init or have a package.json file already there.</li><li>Run: <code>npm install cypress --save-dev</code></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s basically it for installing Cypress, there are some other options available to install it, like using yarn or even a direct download option.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now we will be able to open it: you can use npx or add a specific script into your package.json file.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->\n<ol><li><code>npx cypress open</code></li><li><code>"scripts": { "cy:open": "cypress open" }</code></li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you use option 1 that will be it, and if you choose option 2, you will have to run <code>npm run cy:open</code></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You will see something like this.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {"id":58,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->\n<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/image-1.png" alt="" class="wp-image-58"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are now ready to start writing tests with this wonderful tool.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Reference: <a href="https://docs.cypress.io/guides/getting-started/installing-cypress#Installing" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" title="https://docs.cypress.io/guides/getting-started">https://docs.cypress.io/guides/getting-started</a></em></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Installing Cypress', 'Cypress is a front end testing tool, and according to its documentation, it will allow you to write:\nEnd to end tests (E2E)\nIntegration tests\nUnit tests', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'lets-start-using-cypress', '', '', '2021-05-25 20:56:55', '2021-05-25 20:56:55', '', 0, 'https://darioalejandrodiaz.com/?p=56', 0, 'post', '', 0),
